        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 8:14PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 814 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Radford, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Christiansburg...
Radford...
Pilot...
Shawsville...
Terrys Fork...
and Claytor Dam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
